      "has_lesson_plan": true,
      "relative_position": 15,
      "properties": {
        "overview": "**How will I use what I know about 1D arrays to answer a Free Response Question?**\n\nStudents practice developing solutions to AP CSA FRQs on a mock Arrays FRQ. Students apply decomposition and annotation strategies to identify the key components of the problem and validate their solutions using Scoring Guidelines.",
        "preparation": "* Print copies of the TicketTracker FRQ Graphic Organizer (one for each student)\n* Print copies of the TicketTracker FRQ handout (one for each student)\n* Print copies of the TicketTracker FRQ Scoring Guidelines (one for each student)\n* (Optional) Gather blue, orange, and pink colored pencils or markers for each student\n* Check the [**Teacher's Lounge**](https://forum.code.org/t/csa-3-11-tickettracker-frq/37895) for verified teachers on the CSA Forum to find additional strategies or resources shared by fellow teachers",
        "student_overview": "**How will I use what I know about 1D arrays to answer a Free Response Question?**\n\nIn this lesson, you practice developing solutions to AP CSA FRQs on a mock Arrays FRQ. You apply decomposition and annotation strategies to identify the key components of the problem and validate your solution using Scoring Guidelines."
