    {
      "key": "5b88702e-a602-4a67-868f-c7409b854a01",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned a lot about 1D arrays so far! Let's take a moment to reflect on what we have learned and consider how we can use these with what we already know about Java to solve new problems.",
        "name": "Revisiting Dessert Flavors",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5b88702e-a602-4a67-868f-c7409b854a01",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4151d051-5fe2-4d6e-96eb-6ebd70032685"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "39f702fc-c4e6-49f7-a781-64d293b84d30",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Based on what we now know about 1D arrays, how can we store these values in a program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest declaring and initializing a 1D array and assigning each value to the appropriate position in the array.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate a solution.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 3 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "39f702fc-c4e6-49f7-a781-64d293b84d30",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4151d051-5fe2-4d6e-96eb-6ebd70032685"
      }
    },
