    {
      "key": "456c9bb8-efcd-4bb3-8096-9a8c52add53e",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We now know how to store multiple related values in a 1D array and access individual elements. As the length of our 1D arrays increase, we may need to use more efficient ways to access their elements. ",
        "name": "Finding the Sum",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "456c9bb8-efcd-4bb3-8096-9a8c52add53e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "15fbe33a-f5ca-4ae6-8b13-3abdf30662fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f2fdc22a-f418-41d9-affb-0cc16390e4f7",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Based on what we know about Java, how could we find the sum of all the values in this 1D array?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest creating a variable to store the sum and adding each value in the 1D array to the sum one at a time. Students may recall using `while` loops and suggest looping through the 1D array to add each value to the variable.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f2fdc22a-f418-41d9-affb-0cc16390e4f7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "15fbe33a-f5ca-4ae6-8b13-3abdf30662fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "458567ba-3174-4e94-b97b-1eaa1924eec7",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *If the length of this 1D array was 100, would your solution still work?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students realize that accessing each value in the 1D array one at a time would still work, but it is inefficient. Students might suggest using a loop to repeatedly add each value in the 1D array to the variable instead."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "458567ba-3174-4e94-b97b-1eaa1924eec7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "15fbe33a-f5ca-4ae6-8b13-3abdf30662fb"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7db700ac-bacb-4d1b-904f-07e2e6dc2a04",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7db700ac-bacb-4d1b-904f-07e2e6dc2a04",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "528f4369-5018-491d-9d11-a1800bed3e88",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Accessing each element in a 1D array one at a time can be tedious when there are many elements. Luckily, we can use a structure we have used before in The Neighborhood to access the elements in a 1D array more efficiently!",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "528f4369-5018-491d-9d11-a1800bed3e88",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "79462b3d-c16d-40b8-8fe1-d172f072dcf0",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Traversing 1D Arrays"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "79462b3d-c16d-40b8-8fe1-d172f072dcf0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b60c8bed-c397-49a6-98e2-bbdc2cc6731a",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Discuss: Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that a `while` loop is used to print each element in the 1D array. Students may wonder how the use of the `while` loop is similar to how it was used in The Neighborhood in Unit 1."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b60c8bed-c397-49a6-98e2-bbdc2cc6731a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6ff05236-c12e-48eb-8089-e3b2dcd05729",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "With loops, we can repeat a block of code as long as a condition is `true`. When used with a 1D array, we can repeatedly access each element in a 1D array as long as we are not at the end. Let's take a look at how this works.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Using while Loops",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6ff05236-c12e-48eb-8089-e3b2dcd05729",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "355fe76e-acc2-45a2-9216-d1efff66a1f4",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to recall the syntax and functionality of a `while` loop.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Define ***traverse***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Traversing 1D Arrays"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "355fe76e-acc2-45a2-9216-d1efff66a1f4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4cc80f9f-07e5-4e13-9b46-ed9299eff12f",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Prompt students to share similarities and differences they notice in the way they used a `while` loop in The Neighborhood and the way a `while` loop is used to traverse a 1D array. You can also ask students to share what happens if the variable `index` is not changed in the body of the `while` loop."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4cc80f9f-07e5-4e13-9b46-ed9299eff12f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c6986eaf-387a-480d-b062-6442893b66c0",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Explain the syntax for traversing a 1D array with a `while` loop:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Declaring and initializing a variable before the loop to track the position\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Checking if the variable is less than the length of the 1D array as the loop condition\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Using the variable to access the element at that position in the 1D array\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Increase the variable by one to move to the next element in the 1D array",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Tracing Traversals",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Point out to students that the condition is less than the length of the array rather than less than or equal to its length. Have students identify the length and the last index of the array in the code segment."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c6986eaf-387a-480d-b062-6442893b66c0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "83c4d932-edb5-46b6-8fa6-14e04c639d10",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When we traverse a 1D array using a `while` loop, we need a variable to keep track of where we are in the array. We can compare the current value assigned to this variable to the length of the array to check if we have reached the end, and we have to make sure we are changing this variable so we move forward or backwards a set amount each time the loop repeats. Otherwise, we are stuck on the same element infinitely!",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "83c4d932-edb5-46b6-8fa6-14e04c639d10",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6c0d415c-30c0-4bf3-844c-9e6db1aa618c",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Click through the animated slides to demonstrate traversing a 1D array with a `while` loop:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> First iteration of the loop\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Second iteration of the loop\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Third iteration of the loop\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> End of the loop\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate tracing the code segment.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Model tracing the first two iterations of the loop, then ask students to assist in completing the rest of the trace table."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6c0d415c-30c0-4bf3-844c-9e6db1aa618c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "bc02b4f6-558f-4d2d-a67c-a0c2b51f857a",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students trace the code segment to identify the error and share suggestions for correcting the error.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to explain the `ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException`."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "bc02b4f6-558f-4d2d-a67c-a0c2b51f857a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2220830e-7d74-4a5b-ae0c-bf29d1dadb9f",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Loops are useful for repeating a task as long as a condition is `true`. This means we can repeatedly access and modify elements in a 1D array, and we can even work with multiple 1D arrays at once using a loop!",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Traversing 1D Arrays",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2220830e-7d74-4a5b-ae0c-bf29d1dadb9f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7f961b29-c07e-4b4a-95cc-63992eeca4ed",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5, 6, and 7. Students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to Level 6 to complete a choice level to traverse a 1D array using a `while` loop. On Level 7, students complete a choice level to traverse multiple 1D arrays using a `while` loop.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Traversing 1D Arrays",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding and practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of the key terms and traversing 1D arrays using a `while` loop."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7f961b29-c07e-4b4a-95cc-63992eeca4ed",
        "lesson_activity.key": "4616a9c0-bb97-4e3a-bd06-159591dd18ae"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "17de74b4-384a-412e-bfa9-0478f5e362ce",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have seen how we can sometimes run into errors when working with 1D arrays and loops. Let's take a look at this code segment and see if we can find the error in this code.",
        "name": "Find the Error",
