    {
      "key": "92a1e009-24c4-4c09-b65b-4727aec8a21c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Data helps us find trends and even make predictions about our society. This visual shows us the popularity and revenues of music formats over the years.",
        "name": "Data and the Music Industry",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "92a1e009-24c4-4c09-b65b-4727aec8a21c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "51f5e0d5-2258-4967-907b-fd9a8db13485"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "62cd1233-2370-423e-8589-4047a5c53c70",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How could we store this information in 1D arrays? What would be the data type for each 1D array?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest creating 1D arrays to store the revenue for each year or the revenue for each format. Students note that a 1D array to store the revenue would be declared to store `double` values.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ask students to identify the specific data points in the visual, such as the total revenue for each year and each format. You can also have students consider the appropriate data types for each type of information."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "62cd1233-2370-423e-8589-4047a5c53c70",
        "lesson_activity.key": "51f5e0d5-2258-4967-907b-fd9a8db13485"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "ff885346-9395-435c-9811-538d6542a584",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What surprises you about this data? What questions might someone be able to answer with this data?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students may be surprised that streaming and downloading music has led to decreased revenue in comparison to CDs. Students suggest that a program would add up the values for each year or each format so it could be displayed in this visual.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ff885346-9395-435c-9811-538d6542a584",
        "lesson_activity.key": "51f5e0d5-2258-4967-907b-fd9a8db13485"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1673f026-122c-4320-b238-68ff2aa326f3",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1673f026-122c-4320-b238-68ff2aa326f3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3e99ba11-1d42-4ea7-b9ee-e86934617218",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We previously learned how to traverse a 1D array using a `while` loop so we could access or modify all of its elements. Java also gives us another way to repeat a block of code or traverse a 1D array.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3e99ba11-1d42-4ea7-b9ee-e86934617218",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0bd25bfe-6abb-4e04-9aa2-80bf24a3fd17",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: For Loops"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0bd25bfe-6abb-4e04-9aa2-80bf24a3fd17",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "00a10951-6a40-4a4b-b88c-25d123b4d32b",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice the syntax and functionality of the `for` loop in the program to repeat a block of code. Students might also notice similarities and differences between a `while` loop and the `for` loop and suggest benefits of using a `for` loop. Students may wonder why they might use a `for` loop instead of a `while` loop."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "00a10951-6a40-4a4b-b88c-25d123b4d32b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "78e4c4c5-eca6-48f6-9580-0bba94f7a150",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "In this program, we see an example of a `for` loop that can repeat a block of code. We often can use either a `while` loop or a `for` loop interchangeably, however there are some cases where a `for` loop might be easier to work with for a problem than a `while` loop.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Loops and 1D Arrays",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "78e4c4c5-eca6-48f6-9580-0bba94f7a150",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9c3e7503-2932-4498-b494-4dc5186a4669",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *For Loops*.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9c3e7503-2932-4498-b494-4dc5186a4669",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9bcbfb76-9f7b-491f-bc19-fe289c6cf71e",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: For Loops"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9bcbfb76-9f7b-491f-bc19-fe289c6cf71e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e6c39bdb-04d2-477f-87b2-af448df567d6",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code.\n\n**Do This:** Explain the components of a `for` loop:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Define ***loop control variable***\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> The condition that must be `true` to continue the loop\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> The change of the loop control variable\n\n**Do This:** Explain the functionality of the increment and decrement operators:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Define ***increment*** and introduce the increment operator\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Define ***decrement*** and introduce the decrement operator"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e6c39bdb-04d2-477f-87b2-af448df567d6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a2ba4bda-dd6f-4bcf-95f9-e7f19b1266b8",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate tracing a `for` loop.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Tracing Loops",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Model tracing the first two iterations of the loop, then ask students to assist in completing the rest of the trace table."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a2ba4bda-dd6f-4bcf-95f9-e7f19b1266b8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9d9c826d-4c3a-4fc0-b862-e60fc33c1dfc",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Define ***off-by-one error***:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Introduce the error\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explain the cause of the error\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Explain possible solutions to fix the error",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Have students trace the code segment to identify the error before explaining the off-by-one error. You can also have students suggest solutions to fix the error before discussing the possible solutions."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9d9c826d-4c3a-4fc0-b862-e60fc33c1dfc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0be84ea2-f6f9-4201-a8ea-19e690288bbe",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "A `for` loop has all the same components of a `while` loop but puts all of these components on one line instead of breaking them up across multiple lines of code. This also means we can work with and trace `for` loops the same way we do a `while` loop.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0be84ea2-f6f9-4201-a8ea-19e690288bbe",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "71dec261-19b9-4620-9cab-550c0435447a",
      "position": 12,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Recall the syntax `for` traversing a 1D array with a `while` loop.\n\n**Do This:** Click through the animated slides to demonstrate traversing a 1D array with a `for` loop:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> First iteration\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Second iteration\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Third iteration"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "71dec261-19b9-4620-9cab-550c0435447a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5c278452-201b-4fe6-9624-967e9a5514c6",
      "position": 13,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Since a `for` loop has all the same components of a `while` loop, we can easily convert a `while` loop to a `for` loop or vice versa.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5c278452-201b-4fe6-9624-967e9a5514c6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a4103ab0-1173-422c-825d-43fa84e179fb",
      "position": 14,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students rewrite the code segment traversing a 1D array with a `while` loop using a `for` loop.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to explain the solution."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a4103ab0-1173-422c-825d-43fa84e179fb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d3f15140-a3d4-4e49-b340-7d061938dd88",
      "position": 15,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We now have two types of loops we can use in our programs. We can use either a `while` loop or a `for` loop to repeat a block of code. Both types of loops will repeat as long as a condition is `true` but are structured differently.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Traversing 1D Arrays",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d3f15140-a3d4-4e49-b340-7d061938dd88",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "25dc902b-81c0-4cff-9266-5fe2e3222f71",
      "position": 16,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5, 6, and 7. Students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to Level 6 to complete a choice level to convert a `while` loop to a `for` loop. On Level 7, students complete a choice level to traverse a 1D array using a `for` loop in the console or The Neighborhood.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Using for Loops",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding and practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of the key terms and traversing 1D arrays using a `for` loop."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "25dc902b-81c0-4cff-9266-5fe2e3222f71",
        "lesson_activity.key": "6f75dbcf-736f-4b8e-aef4-0ac892ca7586"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "624be8ba-49d2-4758-82d1-2c955f01d84c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned a lot about `while` loops and `for` loops and how these loops are interchangeable. Depending on the problem we are trying to solve, we might choose to use one type of loop over another.",
        "name": "Design Thinking",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "624be8ba-49d2-4758-82d1-2c955f01d84c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a47b3fde-5f73-47e3-bb08-12b98aba9844"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "531ba3b5-1561-4a13-a724-6951cd817bdd",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Which type of loop would be best for this scenario? Why?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest using a `while` loop because this problem does not have a value that can be used as a loop control variable. Students realize that a `while` loop might be more ideal for this type of scenario because they are unsure how many times the loop might need to repeat.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Which type of loop would be best for this scenario? Why?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest using a `for` loop because this problem has a value that can be used as a loop control variable. Students realize that a `for` loop might be more ideal for this type of scenario because they can determine how many times the loop needs to repeat.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 3 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "531ba3b5-1561-4a13-a724-6951cd817bdd",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a47b3fde-5f73-47e3-bb08-12b98aba9844"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "276ab599-9dcf-4f8f-83e8-74da8401e803",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary"
