    {
      "key": "7ad252aa-9ca6-40d0-a0ee-54e9798c2220",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Computer science involves more than just writing code. Computer science helps us answer questions and solve problems. Data scientists do this by collecting data and analyzing it using algorithms to obtain knowledge.",
        "name": "Data Science",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7ad252aa-9ca6-40d0-a0ee-54e9798c2220",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5bf95548-6aaf-42a4-aa2d-070b53928361"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d315001e-e3ab-40c1-a5e7-f187e9669236",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Careers in Tech: My Name is Polina*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to write down ideas and thoughts in response to the prompt on a sticky note or scrap piece of paper.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Throughout the curriculum, students are exposed to examples of computer science in different industries or problems that could potentially be solved using computer science. These are intended to contribute to the development of their identities as software engineers and challenge their perceptions about who software engineers are and what they do. As you learn about your students and their personal interests, you can change these scenarios to show examples of computer science connected to their personal interests to make these more meaningful for your classroom."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d315001e-e3ab-40c1-a5e7-f187e9669236",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5bf95548-6aaf-42a4-aa2d-070b53928361"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f6e2f748-9a4d-4852-847c-949187bbf18c",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue the Give One, Get One activity and direct students to participate in a Give One, Get One.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue.\n\nGive One, Get One encourages students to seek and share ideas and information. Students circulate the classroom and pair up with a partner when prompted by the teacher. Each student \"gives\" or shares one of their ideas as the other student \"gets\" or listens and writes it down. The teacher then prompts students to find new partners and repeat the process."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f6e2f748-9a4d-4852-847c-949187bbf18c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5bf95548-6aaf-42a4-aa2d-070b53928361"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2fd1804d-7182-4bc1-9cfa-99edfb32858a",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you learn from each other?*\n* *How did these ideas and thoughts contribute to your identity as a software engineer?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share their thoughts and ideas about data science. Students identify aspects that relate or contribute to their identity as software engineers and may wonder about potential careers."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2fd1804d-7182-4bc1-9cfa-99edfb32858a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "5bf95548-6aaf-42a4-aa2d-070b53928361"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "9cba66e3-018c-4f43-9733-175f00ccfa78",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "9cba66e3-018c-4f43-9733-175f00ccfa78",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "671167d2-ffe4-42bf-b348-24cb2cae3d48",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have used `while` loops and `for` loops to repeat blocks of code and traverse 1D arrays. Sometimes a problem will require us to use one type of loop. Other times, they both can be used in different ways to solve the same problem. There is a third type of loop that we can use to traverse a 1D array.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "671167d2-ffe4-42bf-b348-24cb2cae3d48",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c801f708-82a4-4913-87d5-570177e5e4cb",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Enhanced For Loops"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c801f708-82a4-4913-87d5-570177e5e4cb",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3d390089-77a8-4023-8112-bb52c83328a3",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice the structure of the enhanced `for` loop and that it traverses the 1D array. Students may wonder why they would use this loop instead of a `while` or `for` loop."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3d390089-77a8-4023-8112-bb52c83328a3",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fef028a4-a9c2-44a5-aded-e9ca5d7ffc37",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Enhanced For Loops*.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Exploring Enhanced For Loops",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fef028a4-a9c2-44a5-aded-e9ca5d7ffc37",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f5b5c36e-5b6d-408c-bd9e-ff9cd4c88417",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Enhanced For Loops"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f5b5c36e-5b6d-408c-bd9e-ff9cd4c88417",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3265b0cb-4f98-48b3-a78a-b73de252a8a4",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3265b0cb-4f98-48b3-a78a-b73de252a8a4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3fbb2b37-491b-4dd9-9b5f-2d9dd0bf2b05",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "An enhanced `for` loop can be used instead of `for` or `while` loops in many situations, however it does have some limitations because of its functionality. This type of loop is useful when we need to access each element in a 1D array from first to last.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Using Enhanced For Loops",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3fbb2b37-491b-4dd9-9b5f-2d9dd0bf2b05",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5218b14d-1aa5-4837-b785-57a7e1933182",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce enhanced `for` loops and discuss the example.\n\n**Do This:** Explain the components of an enhanced `for` loop:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Declaring a loop control variable\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Stating the name of the array\n\n**Do This:** Explain the functionality of the enhanced `for` loop variable:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> It is assigned a copy of the element.\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> If the element is a primitive value, changing the value of the enhanced `for` loop variable does not modify the element in the array.\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> If the element is an object, calling methods that change the state of an object will modify the values assigned to its instance variables.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5, 6, and 7. Students complete a Check for Understanding on Level 5, then continue to Level 6 to complete a choice level to convert a `while` or `for` loop to an enhanced `for` loop. On Level 7, students complete a choice level to implement an algorithm to find the average of all elements in a 1D array using an enhanced `for` loop.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Traversing 1D Arrays",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding and practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of the key terms and traversing 1D arrays using an enhanced `for` loop."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5218b14d-1aa5-4837-b785-57a7e1933182",
        "lesson_activity.key": "973c89c3-afd9-429b-a953-f1766da2185f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0f5a0338-f9db-4291-aa09-743867b2ef51",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now we have three different loops we can use to traverse a 1D array! We already know when we would want to use a `while` or a `for` loop. Let's take a moment to consider when we would want to use an enhanced `for` loop.",
        "name": "Design Thinking",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0f5a0338-f9db-4291-aa09-743867b2ef51",
        "lesson_activity.key": "20db9491-39c0-4be4-8e13-dd392494bcbe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2e0e586e-2301-42a1-9592-466810f06655",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *When is it best to use an enhanced `for` loop?*\n* *When is it not best to use an enhanced `for` loop?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest scenarios where an enhanced `for` loop would be best to use, such as printing each element in a 1D array from first to last. Students note that since an enhanced `for` loop cannot be used to modify the values in a 1D array, it is best to use either a `for` or a `while` loop when the values need to be modified. Students should also note that if the elements in a 1D array need to be accessed in a different order, either a `for` or `while` loop should be used instead of an enhanced `for` loop.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ask additional probing questions to help students identify what they noticed in the program. For example:\n* *What does an enhanced `for` loop do?*\n* *What happened when you tried to modify the values stored in the array in the enhanced `for` loop?*\n* *Can you start at a specific index instead of at the beginning of the array?*\n* *Is the loop control variable in the enhanced `for` loop referencing the value in the array, or is it making a copy of the value from the array?*"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2e0e586e-2301-42a1-9592-466810f06655",
        "lesson_activity.key": "20db9491-39c0-4be4-8e13-dd392494bcbe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "1489d0e0-2603-4154-b6fb-7095fe2b2e6e",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Explain use cases and limitations for using enhanced `for` loops.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 3 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "1489d0e0-2603-4154-b6fb-7095fe2b2e6e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "20db9491-39c0-4be4-8e13-dd392494bcbe"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c674bc7c-ef52-4c32-b533-db07057db0f3",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
