      }
    },
    {
      "key": "b2d965f8-d7ac-4ffb-a63d-26be2c88749e",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5 and 6. Students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to Level 6 to implement their algorithm to find duplicate values for their chosen problem.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Finding Duplicate Values",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding and practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of the key terms and writing an algorithm using nested loops to traverse a 1D array."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "b2d965f8-d7ac-4ffb-a63d-26be2c88749e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "737d7eb6-cd93-4e2b-b3cf-27a20f9b005c"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "74ff5159-eb3e-43e3-ba90-0bbe3aae4c50",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "name": "Show What You Know Week",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 3 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "74ff5159-eb3e-43e3-ba90-0bbe3aae4c50",
        "lesson_activity.key": "989b3e21-49ba-4c16-b68c-86ef7cd8881f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5157cbf9-c218-44c3-84dd-421266f51f2f",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "The next five lessons are an opportunity to Show What You Know! We begin with the unit project, then spend a day practicing answering AP-style free-response questions and wrapping up the unit with a multiple-choice assessment. You've learned so much in this unit, and now you're ready to show what you know!",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5157cbf9-c218-44c3-84dd-421266f51f2f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "989b3e21-49ba-4c16-b68c-86ef7cd8881f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "366d208d-c2d6-41f1-84a7-e4984be0c33e",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Unit 3 Study Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Show What You Know Week.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Data for Social Good Project.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "366d208d-c2d6-41f1-84a7-e4984be0c33e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "989b3e21-49ba-4c16-b68c-86ef7cd8881f"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3202cfaa-1ed1-4922-8ee2-d5320cc41b95",
