    {
      "key": "4a8e9fd6-143c-4a0d-8269-fd5c5011642b",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "When we write new code, getting feedback from our peers is helpful to make sure we have met the requirements of the problem efficiently.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4a8e9fd6-143c-4a0d-8269-fd5c5011642b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ac3c6bcc-d169-4033-81cd-f7ba6345d497"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f57e0daa-b295-4102-994d-b60d09a1d682",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to have students participate in the Code Review Call and Response.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to conduct a code review on their Data for Social Good Project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Students may be at different points when it is time for the code review. Emphasize to students that their work does not need to be completed to get feedback. Remind students that the problem-solving and development process is iterative and that receiving feedback from peers while they are working can help give them additional insights, perspectives, and guidance."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f57e0daa-b295-4102-994d-b60d09a1d682",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ac3c6bcc-d169-4033-81cd-f7ba6345d497"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "90a5965d-fc19-4d8a-8518-084db0ea26e2",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "You have a lot of feedback from the code review to help improve your program! Let's review our tasks and priorities and plan updates based on the feedback we received and what we have left to complete.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Revisions, Updates, and Reviews",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "90a5965d-fc19-4d8a-8518-084db0ea26e2",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ac3c6bcc-d169-4033-81cd-f7ba6345d497"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "af8b0d8d-40fc-4b62-9e4b-74930943c72b",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students self-assess their project using the program requirements and rubric on the Data for Social Good Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students create a prioritized list of upgrades, changes, and things they still need to complete on the Data for Social Good Project Planning Guide based on the feedback they received from the code review.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If students finish their prioritized list early, encourage them to start working on their #1 priority."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "af8b0d8d-40fc-4b62-9e4b-74930943c72b",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ac3c6bcc-d169-4033-81cd-f7ba6345d497"
      }
    },
    {
