    {
      "key": "ddb81df1-93ef-42a5-8525-82f0f9f171f0",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "After completing this project, students should complete the End of Unit Survey linked in the final level. Their responses help us understand their experiences and improve future versions of this unit.",
        "progression_name": "End of Unit Survey"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "ddb81df1-93ef-42a5-8525-82f0f9f171f0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "e7ee953f-8d8e-4f38-aaab-3ed4bf66eeef"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2642f319-71d4-4887-933e-cb838add0b0a",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Many industries rely on data to identify solutions to problems and make decisions. Each user has different needs based on the information they need and the questions they need to answer.",
        "name": "Users and Data",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2642f319-71d4-4887-933e-cb838add0b0a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a59da2a2-1dbb-403c-9131-c6dfb2f2b166"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "98ce4513-cb8d-42e0-9d8c-eee610e73301",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show the examples of different types of users and their data needs.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What does this make you wonder about how you could create a data analysis program for a user?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students talk about obtaining data related to a user's needs and reading the data into a program. Students present ideas of questions the user might have and algorithms that can find the answers to these questions and how users would interact with the program to choose the information they need."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "98ce4513-cb8d-42e0-9d8c-eee610e73301",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a59da2a2-1dbb-403c-9131-c6dfb2f2b166"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "cb3c4111-9435-496b-91ae-bb7b0268158f",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Data for Social Good Project Planning Guide.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the project requirements.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to read the rubric on pages 2 and 3.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What do you notice about the project requirements and rubric? What does success look like for this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share what they notice about the project requirements and rubric and identify the components to implement in their program.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What barriers do you anticipate to achieving success on this project?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify barriers they anticipate and share any questions they have about the project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "cb3c4111-9435-496b-91ae-bb7b0268158f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a59da2a2-1dbb-403c-9131-c6dfb2f2b166"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "22c98abd-6dab-4966-a579-dd63b7af0c38",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Introduce the user scenarios for the project:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Streaming music customer, avian veterinary student, technology non-profit manager\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Community activist, advertising specialist, choose your own",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "Brainstorming and Planning",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Students can also create their own rather than using one of the provided scenarios."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "22c98abd-6dab-4966-a579-dd63b7af0c38",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2bcbb86d-69f1-4621-ada7-4ac4d75b62b1"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "600c7075-6901-40b9-849c-4d76da1d36e0",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to identify their topic of interest, create UML diagrams for their classes, and identify the questions they want to answer on the Data for Social Good Project Planning Guide.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The classes for each user scenario are created on the corresponding choice level. Have students look at the data sets and files for their selected user stories as they plan their program."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "600c7075-6901-40b9-849c-4d76da1d36e0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2bcbb86d-69f1-4621-ada7-4ac4d75b62b1"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3126c745-8ca9-425e-8c95-2e31da1683dc",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to develop their Data for Social Good Project.",
        "duration": "20",
        "name": "Development",
        "progression_name": "Data for Social Good Project"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3126c745-8ca9-425e-8c95-2e31da1683dc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2bcbb86d-69f1-4621-ada7-4ac4d75b62b1"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "26246201-646e-4ed6-b59a-8a7c5a63e9ba",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our new superclass and subclasses to the Backpack. Anytime we make changes to our programs, it is helpful to commit, or save, our work as a new version in case we need to revert to a previous version.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "26246201-646e-4ed6-b59a-8a7c5a63e9ba",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2bcbb86d-69f1-4621-ada7-4ac4d75b62b1"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "be974241-de45-4bfd-8010-01d10e9acf6a",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue committing their code and saving their classes to the Backpack.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "be974241-de45-4bfd-8010-01d10e9acf6a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "2bcbb86d-69f1-4621-ada7-4ac4d75b62b1"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "252bee43-ec91-423f-be85-56a7bdfb64fe",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the End of Project Reflection prompt on the Data for Social Good Project Planning Guide.",
        "name": "End of Project Reflection",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their thoughts and ideas with a neighbor."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "252bee43-ec91-423f-be85-56a7bdfb64fe",
        "lesson_activity.key": "714b6fd4-a72d-46c2-b5ce-73bb5c2979af"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "0d00c29a-199b-4f0e-840f-9049d03e53ff",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "0d00c29a-199b-4f0e-840f-9049d03e53ff",
